  "texts": [
    "Despite being widely used in practice, collaborative filtering (CF) approaches have several limitations such as data sparsity and the cold-start problem for new items and users.",
    "These limitations negatively impact the quality and accuracy of recommendation predictions.Researchers have frequently chosen to employ hybrid recommendation filtering to achieve improved recommendation quality while also mitigating the limitations associated with traditional Collaborative Filtering (CF) recommendation approaches.",
    "One stream of hybrid recommendation filtering focuses on combining CF filtering algorithms with other RSs techniques, specifically contentbased filtering.",
    "Another stream of hybrid recommendation research has emerged, called semantic-based hybrid filtering, in which it focuses on incorporating the underlying semantics of users or items in the recommendation process [4,8,15].",
    "Such hybrid filtering utilizes semantic Web technologies and features, specifically ontologies, as means that can allow RSs to extract useful knowledge about users or items, which ultimately leads to producing effective predictions."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Another stream of hybrid recommendation research has emerged, called semantic-based hybrid filtering, in which it focuses on incorporating the underlying semantics of users or items in the recommendation process [4,8,15]."
